The correct answer is G. Formation of antibodies to RhD.  

Rho(D) immune globulin is given to Rh-negative mothers to prevent sensitization to the RhD antigen, which can occur if fetal Rh-positive red blood cells enter the maternal circulation. This prevents the mother from forming anti-D antibodies that could cause hemolytic disease of the newborn in future pregnancies.  

